                <mxCell id="note_vo" value="&lt;b&gt;Divergence 1&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;GroomingProfile is stored as a separate table with UNIQUE(patientId). In DDD it is a 1:1 Value Object — it has no identity apart from its Patient and dies with it. Consider folding into Patient columns or a JSONB field." style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=6;spacingTop=4" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="580" y="210" width="210" height="100" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="note_charge" value="&lt;b&gt;Divergence 2&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Charge.sourceId is polymorphic: it references Consultation | Grooming | Procedure | Sale | Hospitalization by string tag only. No FK enforcement. Integrity lives in app code. Consider typed subclasses or a charge-per-source join table." style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;fontSize=10;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=6;spacingTop=4" parent="1" vertex="1">
